The paper deals with the computational complexity of partition functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The use of matrices and fields in the paper suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as possible sub-categories.
